      <data key="v_content">28: &quot;Economy of Chittagong&quot;
James Finlay PLC, BOC Bangldesh Ltd., GEC Bangladesh Ltd., Coats Thread, Berger, KAFCO, and Duncan. Economy of Chittagong The economy of Chittagong is one of the largest and most rapidly growing economies in Bangladesh. As of 2014, Chittagong is home of some of Bangladesh&apos;s and the world&apos;s top corporations. Chittagong is the port-city of Bangladesh and the busiest port in South Asia. Chittagong is the export hub of Bangladesh and it grosses more than $20 billion from export, accounting for 45% of Bangladesh&apos;s national export. In 2014, Chittagong&apos;s gross state product was $41.45 billion in nominal terms and $174.06 billion</data>
