running in 1990 and again in 2017. Especially in winter, southern right whales may provide onlookers chances to witness them cavorting close to shores. Seaspray, Victoria Seaspray is a small coastal town in Victoria, Australia, in the Gippsland region of the state. The town is located alongside the Ninety Mile Beach about off the South Gippsland Highway in the Shire of Wellington, east of the state capital, Melbourne. At the , Seaspray had a population of 316. Seaspray&apos;s main recreational features and tourism attractions focus around swimming, surfing and other watersports, as well as fishing on the Ninety Mile Beach.</data>
