editing, under the pseudonym &quot;&quot;Rab Noolas&quot;&quot; (&quot;&quot;Saloon Bar&quot;&quot; backwards), of &quot;&quot;Merry-Go-Down&quot;&quot;, an anthology in praise of drinking. The book, published by The Mandrake Press, was copiously illustrated by Hal Collins. Early in 1929 Heseltine received two offers from Beecham which temporarily restored his sense of purpose. Beecham had founded the Imperial League of Opera (ILO) in 1927; he now invited Heseltine to edit the ILO journal. Beecham also asked Heseltine to help organise a festival to honour Delius, which the conductor was planning for October 1929. Although Heseltine&apos;s enthusiasm for Delius&apos;s music had diminished, he accepted the assignment, and travelled</data>
