      <data key="v_content">45: Tappet
the valve movement to press the valves downwards to open them. Early tappets had rollers to reduce wear from the rotating camshaft, but it was found that the roller pivots wore even faster and also that the small radius of the rollers also tended to accelerate wear on the expensive camshaft. Tappets then developed plain flat ends, although these were slightly radiused as &apos;mushroom&apos; tappets, since a perfectly flat end led to &apos;slamming&apos; against a steep camshaft face. To reduce wear from the rotating camshaft, the tappets were usually circular and allowed, or even encouraged, to rotate. This avoided grooves</data>
