pace of Harold Larwood and punished Maurice Tate when his bowling strayed down the leg side. In 105 minutes, Jackson and Ryder added 100 runs. Jackson reached his half century, followed by Ryder and at stumps on the second day, Australia&apos;s total was 3/131. The exertion had left Jackson exhausted. His team-mate &quot;&quot;Stork&quot;&quot; Hendry said that Jackson was limp when he returned to the dressing room. &quot;&quot;We had to mop him with cold towels&quot;&quot;, he said. Early the next day, Ryder was dismissed and Jackson was joined by Bradman. The two young batsmen shared a long partnership, with Jackson on</data>
