      <data key="v_content">78: &quot;Arsenal Stadium&quot;
taking the role instead. By the time of Euro 96, the pitch had been ruled too small for international football and the stadium would have been ineligible. Highbury was the venue for twelve FA Cup semi-finals as a neutral ground, the first in 1929 and the last in 1997, although between 1984 and 1992 it was off the FA&apos;s list of approved venues, after Arsenal&apos;s refusal to install perimeter fencing following a pitch invasion by Everton fans during their semi-final against Southampton. It also hosted the London XI&apos;s home leg against Lausanne Sports in the 1955–58 Inter-Cities Fairs Cup semi-finals;</data>
      <data key="v_name">passage-e18dfcce7ece35a957f036bfaf9fb95a</data>
