Linda Thompson (actress) Linda Diane Thompson (born May 23, 1950) is an American songwriter/lyricist, former actress and beauty pageant winner. She was married to Olympic decathlon champion Bruce Jenner (now known as Caitlyn Jenner), and David Foster, musician, record producer, composer, songwriter and arranger. Thompson was born and raised in Memphis, Tennessee, the daughter of Margie (née White) and Sanford Abel Thompson. Her older brother, Sam, was one of Elvis Presley&apos;s bodyguards. Thompson was Miss Shelby County (1969) In September 1970, she was named &quot;&quot;Miss Mid-South Fair&quot;&quot; at Memphis. Some of her other titles are, &quot;&quot;Miss Liberty Bowl&quot;&quot;, &quot;&quot;Memphis State&apos;s</data>
